  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The cornflour in the filling thickens the apple juices as they release during baking, giving a filling that slices cleanly rather than running. Mix it through the raw apple slices before putting them in the pie; it distributes evenly and activates as the filling heats. Let the pie rest for 15 minutes after baking before cutting: cutting too soon gives a liquid filling rather than a set one."
          }
        ]
      },
