            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make the pastry"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Rub the cold butter into the flour, sugar, and salt until the mixture resembles rough crumbs with some butter flakes visible. Add the cold water one tablespoon at a time until the dough just comes together. Divide into two equal pieces. Flatten each into a disc, wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Heat the oven to 200°C fan."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Assemble and bake"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Toss the apple slices with the sugar, cornflour, cinnamon, nutmeg, and lemon juice. Roll one pastry disc to 3 mm and line a 23 cm pie dish. Pile the apple filling in, mounding in the centre. Dot the butter pieces over the apples. Roll the second disc and lay it over the top. Press the edges together, trim the overhang to 2 cm, then fold the edge under itself and crimp all around. Cut 4 or 5 steam vents. Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with the tablespoon of caster sugar. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, until the pastry is deep golden and the filling is bubbling at the vents. Rest for at least 15 minutes before cutting."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
